For caelestia shell

Install Dependencies
Ensure you have Hyprland already running on Triaxis GNU/Linux.

Install required build tools:
sudo apt install git cmake meson ninja-build gcc g++ pkg-config

Install Nix (since Caelestia Shell uses flakes):
curl -L https://nixos.org/nix/install | sh

Clone Caelestia Shell
git clone https://github.com/caelestia-dots/shell.git
cd shell

Build with Nix Flakes
nix build .#caelestia-shell

Enable Hyprland Integration
Caelestia Shell integrates with Hyprland through three layers:

Quickshell Hyprland module (basic workspace/window tracking)

HyprExtras C++ plugin (advanced IPC, device state, events)

Hypr QML service (unified API for UI components)

After building, copy the configuration:

cp -r config ~/.config/caelestia

Launch Caelestia Shell

Start it alongside Hyprland:
caelestia-shell &

Add it to your Hyprland autostart (~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf):
exec-once = caelestia-shell

